text.tspan: Prevalence of undernourishment vs. daily supply of calories, 1991 to 2013
The prevalence of undernourishment, defined as the share of the total population with caloric intakes which fall below
minimum energy requirements, versus the daily supply of calories in kilocalories per person per day. Due to technical
restrictions of the visualisation: data shown as 5% signify a prevalence of undernourishment below 5%.
